-- Carney Says He Intends to Fulfill His Bank of Canada Role
-- B y   G r e g   Q u i n n
-- 2012-04-18T15:47:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-18/carney-says-he-intends-to-fulfill-his-bank-of-canada-role.html
Bank of Canada Governor  Mark Carney 
said he plans to fulfill his responsibilities at the central
bank and as chairman of the Financial Stability Board, and
reiterated that a Financial Times report asserting he was
approached to succeed Bank of England Governor Mervyn King was
not accurate.  Carney made the comments to reporters today in Ottawa.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Greg Quinn in Ottawa at 
 gquinn1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
